parameters:
\nw[Nonna]There might be thieves from here on. If you find
them, make sure to incapacitate them and be
careful not to call for reinforcements.

\nw[Kuno]Yeah, I got it. I'll try to go quietly without
making much noise.
\nw[Nonna]Stop.
\nw[Thief 1]Ahh, being cooped up like this is so boring.
\nw[Thief 2]There's only one woman here. I want more people.

\nw[Nonna]...Thieves, huh? I overheard their conversation,
but someone might be captured.
\nw[Kuno]It seems so... but, the plan is still...
\nw[Nonna]Even if used as a hostage... I'll ignore it...
\nw[Kuno]I knew it...
\nw[Nonna]It's a rule of the Mercenary Guild.

\nw[Nonna]The idea is that if we make it known that
mercenaries are not affected by hostages, then
there won't be anyone who uses hostage tactics
against mercenaries.

\nw[Nonna]That's why we have to prioritize it over our own
emotions.
\nw[Kuno]Yeah, I know... I understand.
\nw[Nonna]......
\nw[Nonna]First, let's neutralize those two. Let's go.
\nw[Kuno]Capture successful, huh.
\nw[Nonna]Well done. You're skilled.
\nw[Thief 1]These guys are nothing special.
\nw[Taro]Ugh...!
\nw[Thief 1]Let's continue like this...

\nw[Nonna]Make sure to fight properly, okay? They weren't
opponents you should lose to, right?
\nw[Taro]Ugh... I'm sorry...

\nw[Nonna]I have something that I was entrusted with by the
owner. I'll give it to you now.
I obtained Heal, Fire, and Hard Attack.
\nw[Taro]What is this?

\nw[Nonna]It seems like a magic ball that allows you to use
skills.

\nw[Taro]Is there such a convenient thing in this
country...

\nw[Nonna]It seems like it's still in the experimental
stage, but it's said to be one of the creations of
a famous magician in this country.

\nw[Nonna]Let me explain it briefly. First, let's start with
how to equip it.
help_eq_001
help_eq_001_2

\nw[Nonna]You can equip the magic ball in the Equipment
menu. It's located in the area surrounded by a red
circle.
\nw[Nonna]However...
help_eq_001_1

\nw[Nonna]The number of slots you can equip is determined by
the total number of Weapon and Body slots. In this
case, you can equip one Short Sword and two
Mercenary Clothes.

\nw[Nonna]Be careful because the number of slots varies
depending on the equipment.

\nw[Nonna]You can only use magic ball skills during battles.
The red magic balls are generally used for
offensive effects.

\nw[Nonna]The blue magic balls have effects such as healing,
support, and hindrance. This one can be used
without consuming a turn, but it takes time to
reuse.

\nw[Nonna]For example, the healing magic ball I gave you
earlier takes 3 turns to reuse.

\nw[Nonna]Healing magic balls take time to reuse and cannot
be used while moving. So it's important to have
plenty of healing items prepared. I also received
some from the owner this time.
I obtained 5 Healing Kits (Single) and 5 Potions.
\nw[Taro]Ah, thank goodness.
\nw[Kuno]That's fine, but...
\nw[Nonna]Is there something that's bothering you?

\nw[Kuno]No, let's do it later. Right now, exterminating
the thieves takes priority, doesn't it?

\nw[Nonna]Yes, that's right. And speaking of that, it's
about the captured girl.

\nw[Nonna]Ignoring them if they become hostages is fine, but
there's no problem with rescuing them before
they're moved.

\nw[Nonna]If we're in a state where we can be ambushed from
here, it's fine. The area doesn't seem too
spacious from the sound, so let's proceed quietly.
\nw[Kuno]Yeah!

You can change the difficulty level in the menu
options. There are four types of difficulty
levels.

Normal -> You can enjoy battles with a satisfying
challenge. Easy -> This difficulty level is for
those who want to progress easily. HP1 -> The
enemy's HP will be reduced to 1. You Win -> You
will achieve victory in battle.

In forced defeat battles, there is no change in
strength based on difficulty level. In You Win
mode, you will automatically be defeated.

\nw[Kuno]This is not the time to be coming out. Let's go
deeper inside.
